news.title: Gauhati HC issues notice to chairperson of Assam RERA
news.para: The court observed, “The issue which has been raised in this PIL is that the Assam Real Estate Regulatory Authority, which is a statutory authority created under the Real Estate (Regulation and Development) Act, 2016 (hereinafter referred to as ‘the Act’) is not functioning in accordance with law.

news.title: Recover cost of demolition from violators in Gurugram: DTCP
news.para: The DTCP enforcement wing issued 46 recovery notices to landowners and builders of illegal colonies on Monday. The total amount sought is nearly Rs 16 lakh. The department would also serve other notices amounting to Rs 10 lakh within a week.

news.title: I-T detects Rs 800-crore cash transactions after raids on Andhra, Telangana realty groups
news.para: ​The unidentified groups are engaged in the business of land development and construction and the taxman raided over two dozen premises linked to them on January 5 in Kurnool, Ananthapur, Kadapa, Nandyal, Bellary and some other locations, it said.

news.title: Gurugram development body likely to seek funds from builders for SPR work
news.para: Chief minister Manohar Lal Khattar, who is also the chairman of the GMDA, has directed officials to now tweak the project to include all of SPR — it was earlier planned for only Golf Course Extension road.

news.title: In Greater Noida, allottees can now get 'no dues' certificates online
news.para: he authority also plans to provide the online service to all industrial, residential, commercial and institutional allotments, with exception of builder allotments.

news.title: Before transfer to MCG, DLF tells Haryana CM yet to recover Rs 77 crore from phase 1-3
news.para: DLF has written to chief minister Manohar Lal Khattar, saying it is yet to recover Rs 77 crore from residents of phases 1, 2 and 3 that are to be transferred to the corporation for maintenance, a takeover process that began in 2019 but is yet to materialise.

news.title: Crib raises $400,000 in pre-seed round
news.para: Headquartered in Gurugram, Crib is building India's first digital ecosystem aimed at redefining how landlords operate, tenants stay and market sells.

news.title: Blackstone exits Mindspace Business Parks REIT; sells stake for Rs 1,740 crore
news.para: Blackstone-entity BREP Asia SG Pearl Holding NQ Pte Ltd sold nearly 5.43 crore units of Mindspace Business Parks REIT worth Rs 1,737.32 crore.

news.title: Registration of homes in Kolkata down 10% in December 2021: Report
news.para: During the entire last year, as many as 44,940 units were registered as compared to 27,328 units in the 2020 calendar year. The consultant noted that 56 per cent of these units were registered since the introduction of the stamp duty cut in July 2021.

news.title: UK gives housebuilders $5 billion bill to remove cladding
news.para: The government has already committed around 5 billion pounds for repairs so far, and last year imposed a levy on housebuilders to raise 2 billion pounds towards the cost over the next 10 years.

news.title: Shimao Group puts residential projects on sale as China property woes deepen
news.para: The Shanghai-based property developer has struck a preliminary deal with a Chinese state-owned company to sell its Shimao International Plaza Shanghai, a commercial property on Shanghai's Nanjing Road, for more than 10 billion yuan, the report said.

news.title: Modern Land shares dive after some bondholders demand early repayment
news.para: Modern Land said in a filing on Monday it has received notices from certain noteholders demanding early repayment of their senior notes, after the firm missed payment for its 12.85% notes due Oct 25, 2021.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh CM to launch housing layouts for MIG on January 11
news.para: The government is readying layouts for the sale of affordable plots in all municipal towns and cities. Urban Development Authorities (UDAs) in the respective districts have been designed as the nodal agencies to take up the MIG smart township projects.

news.title: Kochi: KIIFB appointed consultants for smart city amidst row
news.para: “There are anomalies in roping in KIIFB. The agency lacks experience as a consultant. After issuing the tender, the government changed the tender conditions for giving upper hand to KIIFB,” said Manu Jacob, a UDF councillor in Kochi corporation.

news.title: Sunteck Realty sales bookings rise marginally to Rs 352 crore in Q3 FY22
news.para: During April-December period of the current fiscal, Sunteck Realty's sales bookings grew by 23 per cent to Rs 800 crore from Rs 651 crore in the corresponding period of the previous year.
